This paper deals with inapproximability results for submodular maximization problems, which are typically studied in the context of algorithms and complexity theory. The most relevant sub-category is cs.DS (Data Structures and Algorithms), which is the primary area of research for submodular optimization. The paper also involves concepts from computational complexity (cs.CC), game theory (cs.GT), information theory (cs.IT), and machine learning (cs.LG), which are all related to submodular optimization in different ways.
